    "Both testing capabilities are included in the runtime post-processing of outputs further elaborated in Section 4.3.We have defined the following well-formed rules to guardrail the construction of output testing rules:context ByExpression inv NotSelfValidation: let selfAsset: Set(ByExpression) = self.output.asset -> asSet() in selfAsset -> union(selfAsset -> closure(priorVersion)) -> union(selfAsset -> closure(refines)) -> union(selfAsset -> closure(equivalents)) -> excludes(self.validator) context ByExpression inv ValidatorType: self.validator.oclIsTypeOf(Prompt) or self.validator.oclIsTypeOf(Chain) context ByExpression inv OutputFormat: self.validator.output.type = Media::Text context ByExpression inv ValidatorDoesNotHaveValidation: self.validator.output.outputTestingRule -> isEmpty() context ByReinforcedTrait inv ConsistentTrait: self.output.asset = self.predefinedTrait.prompt Fig. 3 Output testing techniques Concrete syntaxWe have defined a textual syntax to encode specifications written in the Impromptu DSL.",
